Josh,<br><br>
I appreciate your candor and saying what you think and feel.  So many don't.  On the other hand if you are looking for justification of your support of this country with you attitude that some other poor bastard must die to preserve your rights and freedom from terror.  I can't buy it.  On one hand you say you now understand and are just as focused as before.  I guess your problem is definitely not ignorance but a real lack of what it takes to pay the price for those things that history has proven do not come cheap.<br><br>
Our sons are died in many efforts defending not this country but the ideals of those who were more interested in rhetoric than action.  I too have two sons and by no means wish them to die in the war.  They are men they will make their own decisions influenced only by the values they learned while under my roof.<br><br>
If we all followed your lead we would not have the freedom to use this forum today.<br><br>
Cowardice is not an unforgivable failing, but the solicitation of others to your cause is.  Maybe you should go back to Canada and stop stealing the rewards you didn’t earn.  Another type of cowardice is manifested in your actions.<br><br>
When the wolves come to your door help may not be available.<br>

